1. Kupila sam novu torbu za *lovu*. (I bought a new bag for money.)
2. Moram da zaradim malo *love*. (I need to earn some money.)
3. Ne mogu da odem na odmor ove godine, nemam dovoljno *love*. (I can't go on vacation this year, I don't have enough money.)
4. On je pravi *lovac* na novac. (He is a real money hunter.)
5. Večeras idemo u kafanu da se provodimo i trošimo *lovu*. (Tonight we're going to a tavern to have fun and spend money.)
6. Ovaj posao mi donosi dobru *lovu*. (This job brings me good money.)
7. *Lova* je uzrok mnogih problema. (Money is the cause of many problems.)
8. Danas sam pronašla nekoliko kovanica na ulici, imam malo *love* u džepu. (Today I found a few coins on the street, I have some money in my pocket.)
9. On je upravo dobio veliku količinu *love* na lutriji. (He just won a large amount of money in the lottery.)
10. Tražim posao koji će mi obezbediti stabilnu *lovu*. (I'm looking for a job that will provide me with a stable income.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "lova" is a colloquial term for money. It can be used as a noun, verb, or adjective.